      "date": "2022-09-27 16:24:34.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nDoes this logic only kick in when we open the minimum 3 connections in typed mode? If not, should it?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "bba25f2195b5eb998b1e9128905c16e270f03194",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 824,
        "name": "Serguei Smirnov",
        "email": "ssmirnov@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "ssmirnov"
      },
      "date": "2022-09-27 16:50:00.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Does this logic only kick in when we open the minimum 3 connections\n > in typed mode? If not, should it?\n\nThe logic addresses the situation when EALREADY is received (hardcoded N=3) N times in a row regardless of connection type. The assumption is that if EALREADY is received N times in a row, it is not because of the valid \"race\", but because of maxing out connections on the passive side, e.g. valid \"race\" should get resolved sooner. So there's no point in retrying the same connection forever due to EALREADY. Different non-success rc starts exponetial retry timeout increase mechanism, so it is not affected by this logic.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
